    <title>Conserved charges in AdS: A new formula</title>
    <summary>  We give a new construction of conserved charges in asymptotically anti-de
Sitter spacetimes in Einstein's gravity. The new formula is explicitly
gauge-invariant and makes direct use of the linearized curvature tensor instead
of the metric perturbation. As an example, we compute the mass and angular
momentum of the Kerr-AdS black holes.
</summary>
